            <p>Montreal April 2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> 1851.<lb/>
                Mr S Morais<lb/>
                Philadelphia<lb/>
                My dear Sir.<lb/></p>
                <p>Hearing of your arrival<lb/> on this continent I cannot refrain<lb/> bidding you a hearty welcome&#59;<lb/> although it is decreed that for<lb/> a short period we stand once<lb/> again friendly opponents.  It<lb/> would afford me great pleasure<lb/> could I renew in person our<lb/> intimacy formed in England&#44; but<lb/> as this cannot be for the present<lb/> I trust should you make<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/> 
                <p>America the land of your adoption<lb/> that you will favor me with<lb/> a line occasionally to inform<lb/> me of your welfare.<lb/></p>
                <p>Believe me<lb/>
                Yours very faithfully<lb/>
                Abraham de Sola<lb/>
                &#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/></p>
            
        </body>
